02:52.906 --> 02:55.743
Thank you,mrs. Rousso.

02:55.776 --> 02:57.878
I'm sorryabout your dad.

02:57.911 --> 02:59.580
I'm reallygonna miss his,

02:59.613 --> 03:02.516
"you'll never guesswho came into the store,"

03:02.550 --> 03:04.218
stories.

03:08.489 --> 03:10.891
Me, too.

03:10.924 --> 03:13.193
Okay, man.I'll see ya.

03:24.204 --> 03:26.206
Okay, Jake.Why don't you startin the attic,

03:26.240 --> 03:28.876
and I'll startout here in front.

03:28.909 --> 03:30.511
Okay.

03:32.446 --> 03:34.315
I just wantto get this done.

03:56.304 --> 03:58.606
Crazy old grandpa.

04:00.974 --> 04:04.678
I bet there'snot one thing up hereworth anything.

04:27.968 --> 04:30.338
Mom? mom?

04:32.306 --> 04:34.742
What is this?

04:34.775 --> 04:35.976
A wooden box.

04:36.009 --> 04:38.245
I know, but...

04:38.278 --> 04:41.382
Is it a jewelry boxor something?

04:41.415 --> 04:44.518
I don't know,bring it down hereso I can see it.

04:50.524 --> 04:54.294
No, I don't think so.

04:54.328 --> 04:56.330
It feels like there'ssomething in it.

04:57.898 --> 04:59.500
It is pretty heavy.

05:02.002 --> 05:05.539
It can't bethe wood.

05:05.573 --> 05:06.974
I don't know, Jake.

05:07.007 --> 05:09.343
Can I have it?

05:09.377 --> 05:12.946
Of course you can.

05:12.980 --> 05:15.349
You didn't feel anythingwhen you opened it?

05:15.383 --> 05:18.419
No. why?

05:18.452 --> 05:20.320
I did.

05:20.354 --> 05:22.390
It was really weird.

05:22.423 --> 05:24.425
Maybe it wasgrandpa telling youto leave his stuff alone.

05:24.458 --> 05:25.759
You know howhe could always tell

05:25.793 --> 05:28.829
when somethingwas moved.

05:28.862 --> 05:30.998
I bet he wasabout to put it outon the floor.

05:36.370 --> 05:38.005
I'm supposed to meet upwith David and playsome basketball.

05:38.038 --> 05:39.640
Okay, honey.

05:39.673 --> 05:42.576
I'll call you later.See ya.

05:42.610 --> 05:44.512
See ya.

06:03.096 --> 06:05.466
I miss youso much, dad.

06:20.681 --> 06:22.816
Think that we canget to that courtwithout any trouble?

06:22.850 --> 06:25.653
( Basketball bouncing )

06:25.686 --> 06:28.756
Yeah. yeah,i think so.

06:28.789 --> 06:31.024
I guess it'sworth a shot, right?

06:31.058 --> 06:32.926
Come on.Let's' go.

06:38.031 --> 06:41.401
Wait. hey.Hey.

06:41.435 --> 06:42.703
Well, if itisn't captain wannabee

06:42.736 --> 06:44.438
and his littlesidekick.

06:44.472 --> 06:46.507
( Laughs )

06:46.540 --> 06:48.742
Look, we just wantto know if--

06:48.776 --> 06:50.544
you wantto know what, jakey?

06:50.578 --> 06:51.912
Look you guys,we don't want any trouble.

06:51.945 --> 06:53.814
Hey Richie, these guysbothering you?

06:53.847 --> 06:55.683
Nah, man.

06:55.716 --> 06:58.819
These two clownscame over here toask us a question.

06:58.852 --> 07:02.523
They can't seemto spit it out, man.

07:02.556 --> 07:03.957
So what's up, Jake?

07:03.991 --> 07:06.126
You need somethingfrom Richie?

07:06.159 --> 07:08.996
Look, we're tryingto play basketball

07:09.029 --> 07:11.098
in the other court.That's all.

07:11.131 --> 07:15.135
Isn't there a jump ropearound here that you girlscan go play with?

07:15.168 --> 07:17.638
( Laughs )

07:17.671 --> 07:20.974
Why aren't youout somewhere playingwith your grandpa?

07:21.008 --> 07:22.943
( Scoffs )

07:22.976 --> 07:24.512
Come on guys,let's go.

07:30.518 --> 07:32.686
Whoa, buddy.

07:32.720 --> 07:34.722
Look at them.

07:34.755 --> 07:37.558
There's a whole lot of them,and just two of us.

07:37.591 --> 07:40.761
Man, why do we causetrouble all the time?

07:40.794 --> 07:41.995
We can just go playsomewhere else.

07:42.029 --> 07:45.866
Oh yeah?And where wouldthat be, David?

07:45.899 --> 07:47.000
There's not onegood court around here

07:47.034 --> 07:48.902
for milesand you know that.

07:52.606 --> 07:55.108
We can't play ball anyway,your shoe's untied.

07:56.944 --> 07:59.146
( Murmurs )whatever man.

08:03.751 --> 08:05.786
Jake?what's in your bag?

08:05.819 --> 08:08.121
What? oh.

08:08.155 --> 08:11.158
It's just some boxi found in my grandpa'sshop.

08:11.191 --> 08:13.126
But, hey, check it out.

08:19.767 --> 08:21.769
Is there somethingin it?

08:21.802 --> 08:23.671
- It feels likethere's something in it.- Open it.

08:32.245 --> 08:35.783
There's nothing in it.

08:35.816 --> 08:37.650
You don't feel anythingwhen you open it?

08:37.684 --> 08:39.519
- What do you mean?- Never mind.

08:39.553 --> 08:41.621
( Cell phone rings )

08:41.655 --> 08:44.457
Let's head back home.

08:44.491 --> 08:48.228
( Cell phone rings )

08:48.261 --> 08:49.763
Hey, mom.

08:49.797 --> 08:51.498
I'll be homein a couple of hours.

